<subSubSection id="C350656FAE32FFABFF253804FACBD511" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE32FFABFF253804FACBD511" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFF253804FED1D2ED" bold="true" box="[199,315,871,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE32FFABFCF63804FC23D2EC" box="[788,969,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFCF63804FC23D2EC" box="[788,969,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">O. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but may be separated from the latter by the following features: first flagellomere 7.2 times longer than wide; pedicel and first flagellomere dark brown, scape blackish (first flagellomere yellowish brown, paler than brownish scape and pedicel in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE32FFABFB3738CCFA61D2A4" box="[1237,1419,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFB3738CCFA61D2A4" box="[1237,1419,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">O. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pterostigma shorter, trapezoidal, more oblique at outer margin; mesonotum with black bristles (yellow bristles in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE32FFABFF753894FEA0D57C" box="[151,330,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFF753894FEA0D57C" box="[151,330,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">O. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); base of halter brown (yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE32FFABFD243894FC93D57C" box="[710,889,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFD243894FC93D57C" box="[710,889,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">O. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). This new species may be easily separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE32FFABFF753F78FED1D558" authority="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang, 2022" authorityName="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,315,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFF753F78FED1D558" box="[151,315,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">Oedalea yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFEA03F78FE76D559" bold="true" box="[322,412,1051,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D578DAE32FFABFEA03F78FE76D559" box="[322,412,1051,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the antenna rather short, 1.3 times longer than head height (antenna 1.8 times as long as head height in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE32FFABFED93F5CFE71D534" authority="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang, 2022" authorityName="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[315,411,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFED93F5CFE71D534" box="[315,411,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">O. yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFE403F5CFE11D535" bold="true" box="[418,507,1087,1113]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D578DAE32FFABFE403F5CFE11D535" box="[418,507,1087,1113]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
); first flagellomere 7.2 times longer than wide (first flagellomere 12.0 times longer than wide in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE32FFABFECB3F00FE63D510" authority="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang, 2022" authorityName="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[297,393,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFECB3F00FE63D510" box="[297,393,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">O. yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFE723F00FE00D511" bold="true" box="[400,490,1123,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D578DAE32FFABFE723F00FE00D511" box="[400,490,1123,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
); halter dark brown with brown base (halter yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE32FFABFBB23F00FB5AD510" authority="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang, 2022" authorityName="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1104,1200,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFBB23F00FB5AD510" box="[1104,1200,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">O. yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE32FFABFB553F00FAFBD511" bold="true" box="[1207,1297,1123,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D578DAE32FFABFB553F00FAFBD511" box="[1207,1297,1123,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C350656FAE32FFABFF253FE4FC04D5CD" box="[199,1006,1159,1185]" pageId="4" pageNumber="557" type="etymology">
